By Deji Elumoye The Senate on Tuesday asked all the service chiefs to resign forthwith over deteriorating security situation in the country. This was sequel to the adoption of a point of order moved by the Chairman of the Senate Committee on Army, Senator Ali Ndume, over the recent killing of soldiers by insurgents. According to him, the service chiefs should bow out honourably as they have been overwhelmed by rising insecurity situation in the country. Details laterâ€¦